Initial Diagnosis:
- Gather detailed symptom description from user
- Determine when the issue started
- Ask about any recent changes (updates, drops, spills)
- Identify device make, model, and asset tag

Remote Troubleshooting:
- Check if device is powered on and receiving power
- Verify power adapter and cable connections
- Attempt remote connection to diagnose software issues
- Run built-in diagnostics if available

{% if issue_type == 'wont_boot' %}
Boot Failure Steps:
- Check for POST beep codes or LED indicators
- Attempt boot to safe mode
- Test with external monitor if display issue suspected
- Check BIOS/UEFI for hardware detection
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'slow_performance' %}
Performance Steps:
- Check CPU/RAM/Disk usage in Task Manager
- Scan for malware and unwanted software
- Review startup programs and disable unnecessary ones
- Check available disk space
- Verify system is up to date
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'overheating' %}
Overheating Steps:
- Check if vents are blocked or dusty
- Verify fans are operating
- Review running processes for high CPU usage
- Check thermal paste condition if applicable
{% endif %}

Hardware Assessment:
- Run hardware diagnostics (Dell SupportAssist, HP Diagnostics, etc.)
- Document any error codes or failures
- Determine if repair or replacement is needed

Resolution:
- Perform necessary repairs or schedule technician visit
- If replacement needed, initiate equipment request
- Backup user data before any hardware work
- Document resolution and update asset records
